### Configure Blocks Feature in Payload CMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/official-features.mdx

Defines the BlocksFeature for integrating Payload's Blocks Field directly into the editor. This feature allows users to insert content blocks via toolbar buttons and slash menu entries, supporting both standard and inline blocks with custom fields.

```typescript
type BlocksFeatureProps = {
  blocks?: (Block | BlockSlug)[] | Block[]
  inlineBlocks?: (Block | BlockSlug)[] | Block[]
}
```

--------------------------------

### Example Usage of Blocks Feature in Payload CMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/official-features.mdx

Illustrates how to configure the BlocksFeature in Payload CMS, enabling custom block types within the editor. This example defines a 'callout' block with a 'text' field and an 'mention' inline block with a 'name' field.

```typescript
BlocksFeature({
  blocks: [
    {
      slug: 'callout',
      fields: [
        {
          name: 'text',
          type: 'text',
          required: true,
        },
      ],
    },
  ],
  inlineBlocks: [
    {
      slug: 'mention',
      fields: [
        {
          name: 'name',
          type: 'text',
          required: true,
        },
      ],
    },
  ],
})
```

